China Shenhua, Ping An, Zhongjin Gold, Shenzhen Bank: China Equity Preview

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-08-18T00:46:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-17/china-shenhua-ping-an-zhongjin-gold-china-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in  China  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close.  The Shanghai Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, fell 0.3 percent to 2,601.26. The  CSI
300 Index (SHSZ300)  lost 0.4 percent to 2,886.01.  Developers: China’s housing ministry is studying a long-
term development policy for the nation’s property market,
Shanghai Securities News reported today, citing an unidentified
person. The policy will include fiscal, tax and land sale
systems and product innovations such as real estate investment
trusts, according to the newspaper.  China Vanke Co. (000002 CH), the nation’s largest developer
by market value, declined 1.7 percent to 8.22 yuan. Poly Real
Estate Group Co. slid 0.4 percent to 11.05 yuan.  China Shenhua Energy Co. (601088 CH): China’s largest coal
miner said first-half profit rose 16 percent after it acquired
assets to expand production. Net income rose to 21.9 billion
yuan ($3.43 billion) from a restated 18.8 billion yuan a year
earlier. The shares fell 1.4 percent to 27.29 yuan.  China XD Electric Co. (601179 CH): The nation’s biggest
maker of electricity transmission and distribution equipment
said first-half net income fell 93 percent from the same period
a year ago to 35.9 million yuan. The stock gained 0.8 percent to
5.07 yuan.  Guangzhou Baiyun International Airport Co. (600004 CH): The
operator of Guangzhou’s city airport said passenger traffic in
July rose 9.4 percent from a year earlier to 3.6 million, while
cargo shipments gained 1.1 percent to 95,099 tons. The stock
lost 5.2 percent to 7.19 yuan.  Laiwu Steel Corp. (600102)  (600102 CH): The Shandong-based
steelmaker said net income in the first half fell 27 percent
from a year earlier to 198.1 million yuan. The shares retreated
0.1 percent to 8.22 yuan.  Ping An Insurance (Group) Co. (601318 CH): China’s second-
biggest insurer said first-half profit rose 33 percent to 12.8
billion yuan, or 1.67 yuan a share, from 9.61 billion yuan, or
1.30 yuan a share, a year earlier. The shares fell 1.7 percent
to 41.87 yuan on Aug. 16, before trading was halted yesterday.  Shenzhen Development Bank Co. (000001)  (000001 CH): The lender plans
to raise as much as 20 billion yuan by selling additional shares
to Ping An Insurance (Group) Co. in a private placement,
according to an e-mailed statement. First-half net income rose
56 percent from a year ago to 4.7 billion yuan, it said. The
shares fell 0.5 percent to 17.05 yuan on Aug. 16, before trading
was halted yesterday.  Zhongjin Gold Co. (600489 CH): The country’s second-largest
bullion producer by market value raised 2.8 billion yuan in a
sale of about 112 million A-shares for 24.97 yuan each in a
private placement, the company said in a filing to the  Shanghai
Stock Exchange . The shares will become tradable on Nov. 12,
2012, the company said. The stock slid 1.5 percent to 28.84
yuan.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  